---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout>

    <h1>About</h1>

    <section class="section_about_1">
        <div class="img_div"><img class="img1" src="public/assets/imgs_about/about_image_1.png" alt="Sophia and Frederik"></div>
        <div class="text_div"><p class="text_about_1">Our target audience is anyone with a curiosity for food. 
            From those seeking a dedicated caterer, to home cooks looking for recipes </p></div>
    </section>

    <section class="section_about_2">
        <h2>OUR MISSION</h2>
        <p>Studio Cicróne is a culinary studio founded by siblings Sophia and Frederik. We focus on plant-based, organic food that supports both human health and the environment. With hands-on cooking and deep food system knowledge, we craft experiences that nurture people and planet.
Rooted in Food Studies and our family kitchen, we see cooking as a way to connect, celebrate the seasons, and explore creativity. Growing up, food was our joyful playground — experimenting, baking, and working with what was in season.
  After years abroad, we’ve reunited in Copenhagen to share our passion, skills, and love for wholesome food. At Studio Cicróne, we offer more than meals — we offer experiences that educate, inspire, and build community. Workshops, recipes, retreats, and catering all reflect our dedication to quality, sustainability, and joyful connection.
    For us, food isn’t just about taste — it’s about connection to each other, to nature, and to how we live.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="section_about_3">

        <div class="profile_1">

            <div class="profile-text_1">
              <h3>Sophia or Sofia Citron “I love to cook and bake, to eat, and to play.”</h3>
              <p>
                Inspired by people, family, and her studies in holistic nutrition and food science, she sees cooking as a form of cultural activism —
                a way to reconnect people with nature, support food sovereignty, and cultivate a healthy, colorful, and caring food culture.
                She is our cake and dessert master and loves to experiment with grandma's cakes or layer chocolate ganache desserts.
              </p>
              <img src="public/assets/imgs_index/index_graphic-element.svg" alt="Graphic element">
            </div>
            <img src="/assets/imgs_about/about_img_2.png" alt="Sophia Citron - Owner">

          </div>                

          <div class="profile_2">

            <div class="profile-text_2">
              <h3>Frederik is our focaccia and sauce master</h3>
              <p>
                He has a gift for layering flavors and creating bold, unexpected combinations — often with a no-waste mindset. 
                During his studies, 
                he specialized in food waste and continues to explore creative ways to reuse ingredients and cook more sustainably.
            </p> 
            <img src="public/assets/imgs_index/index_graphic-element.svg" alt="Graphic element"> 
          </div>
              <img src="/assets/imgs_about/about_img_3.png" alt="Frederik - Co-owner">
          </div>   

</section>

</Layout>

<style>

  h1{
    margin-top: 6rem;
  }

.section_about_1 {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    margin: 0px auto 60px auto;
    max-width: 450px;
}

.img1 {
    display: flex;
  height: 235px;
  padding-right: 20px;
}

.text_div{
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    max-width: 150px;
}

.text_about_1{
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 27.5px;
    border-left: 3px solid black;
    padding: 20px 0px 20px 10px;
}

.section_about_2 {
  max-width: 350px;    
  margin: 0 auto;
  padding-bottom: 50px ; 
  line-height: 28.5px;       
}

h2{
    text-align: center;
    padding-bottom: 40px;
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    color: #012FA8;
